{
  "doc_id": "11340",
  "text": "For this reason, several analytical methods have been reported for formaldehyde determination including gas chromatography [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , high-performance liquid chromatography [CITATION_3] , capillary electrophoresis [CITATION_4] , enzyme-based biosensors [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] , gas sensors based on metal oxides [CITATION_8] 17, [CITATION_9] and piezoelectric sensors [CITATION_10] [CITATION_11] [CITATION_12] . These methods all however require expensive and laboratory-based apparatus, cannot undertake real-time measurements and are able to only determine a single sample per test.",
